==English==
===Etymology===
From Arabic {{ARchar|[[صحراوي]]}} (ṣaḥrāwi) ‘of the desert’, from {{ARchar|[[صحراع]]}} (ṣaḥrā‘) ‘desert’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/sə'rɑ:wi/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|Sahrawi|Sahrawis}}

# A person from [[Western Sahara]] (formerly Spanish Shara)

====Translations====
*German: [[Sahraoui]] ''m,f''

===Adjective===
'''Sahrawi'''

# Of, from, or pertaining to Western Sahara, the Sahrawi people or the Sahrawi language.

====Translations====
*German: [[der Westsahara]]